        "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-9c6670 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-e3b0c4 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000239\"><span class=\"label\">[17]</span></$link> The one exception to this statement, so far as I know, is the species of silk mosaic made by the ladies in the <i>daimiōs'</i> houses. (<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000388\">See chap. vii.</$link>)</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000273": {
