            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-9c6670 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-e3b0c4 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\">\n</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-9c6670 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-e3b0c4 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\">\n</div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-9c6670 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-e3b0c4 twpub-6a4248ca8f6e64ca-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"footnotes\"><div class=\"footnote\"><p><a></a><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000437\"><span class=\"label\">[37]</span></$link> The samurai always wore two swords, a long one for fighting only, and a short one for defense when possible, but, as a last resort, for <i>hara-kiri</i>. The sword is the emblem of the samurai spirit, and as such is respected and honored. A samurai took pride in keeping his swords as sharp and shining as was possible. He was never seen without the two swords, but the longer one he removed and left at the front door when he entered the house of a friend. To use a sword badly, to harm or injure it, or to step over it, was considered an insult to the owner.</p></div></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/6a4248ca8f6e64ca/text/000000466",
